<p>
  Kiwi is number 10 on the Environmental Working Group's Clean List, but this only includes "Fuzzy" kiwi.  They have a harder, less porous exterior that doesn't soak up a huge amount of the harmful sprays, and you peel this fruit - you don't eat the skin. 
</p>
<p class="cn">
		奇异果在国际工作小组的安全食物清单上排名第10，但是研究仅仅包含了“有毛”的奇异果。它们有着更坚实的表皮，更少的气孔，对有毒喷雾的吸收量较少，而且当你食用它们的时候，你会去皮。
</p>

<p>
	The general rule of thumb is to spend your organic budget on items that have consumable, thin skins that can be permeated by organophosphates.  Kiwiberries fall into this category. 
</p>
